I know, responding to a very old post, but this needs to be said.

This is a setting where things that violate natural laws not only exist, but are implicitly quite commonplace away from the eyes of the general populace. And the Foundation regularly makes use of science and technology that is either explicitly anomalous in nature or is simply far more  than what modern-day human society is capable of, such as drugs that make you forget whatever the Foundation wants you to forget (it's often implied that the induced amnesia can be selective). It's not outside the realm of possibility that the Foundation has methods/tools of anomalous/super-advanced nature that genuinely make torture a relatively viable method of interrogation.







